4 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
5 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
6 Article – Courts and Judicial Proceedings
7 5–106.
8 (a) Except as provided by this section, § 1–303 of the Environment Article, and §
9 8–1815 of the Natural Resources Article, a prosecution for a misdemeanor shall be
10 instituted within 1 year after the offense was committed.
11 (JJ) A PROSECUTION FOR A VIOLATION OF § 10–404(A) OR (B) OF THE
12 CRIMINAL LAW ARTICLE RELATING TO THE DESTRUCTION OF FUNERARY OBJECTS
13 AND OTHER ELEMENTS OF A CEMETERY SHALL BE INSTITUTED WITHIN 3 YEARS
14 AFTER THE LOCAL AUTHORITIES IN FACT KNEW OR REASONABLY SHOULD HAVE
15 KNOWN OF THE VIOLATION.
16 Article – Criminal Law
17 10–404.
18 (a) (1) Subject to the provisions of paragraph (2) of this subsection, a person
19 may not willfully destroy, damage, deface, or remove:
20 (i) an associated funerary object or another structure placed in a
21 cemetery; [or]
22 (ii) a building, wall, fence, railing, or other work, for the use,
23 protection, or ornamentation of a cemetery; OR
24 (III) LANDSCAPING OR PART OF THE GROUNDS OF A CEMETERY.
25 (2) The provisions of paragraph (1) of this subsection do not prohibit the
26 removal of a funerary object or a building, wall, fence, railing, LANDSCAPING, or other
27 object installed for the use, protection, or ornamentation of a cemetery or burial site, for
28 the purpose of repair or replacement, either at the request of or with the permission of heirs
29 or descendants of the deceased or the owner or manager of the cemetery or burial site.
30 (b) (1) Subject to the provisions of paragraph (2) of this subsection, a person
31 may not willfully destroy, damage, or remove a tree, plant, or shrub in a cemetery.

