1 (2) The provisions of paragraph (1) of this subsection do not prohibit
2 normal maintenance of a cemetery or burial site, including trimming of trees and shrubs,
3 removal of weeds or noxious growths, grass cutting, or other routine care and maintenance.
4 (d) A person who violates this section is guilty of a misdemeanor and on conviction
5 is subject to:
6 (1) for a violation of subsection (a) of this section, imprisonment not
7 exceeding 5 years or a fine not exceeding $10,000 or both; and
8 (2) for a violation of subsection (b) or (c) of this section, imprisonment not
9 exceeding 2 years or a fine not exceeding $500 or both.
10 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect
11 October 1, 2025.

